HB 916 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Muscarello
Abstract: Provides for an additional filing fee for recordation of documents with the clerk
of court.
Present law creates the La. Clerks' Remote Access Authority (LCRAA) to provide for
infrastructure, governance, standard operating procedures, technology, and training to
support a statewide portal for secure remote access to certain records maintained by its
members.
Present law authorizes LCRAA to provide assistance to members in procuring,
implementing, enhancing, and maintaining technology-related equipment, supplies, and
services; facilitating electronic transactions and communications; disseminating information
to the public; and supporting operations during declared emergencies.
Proposed law retains present law and authorizes the La. Supreme Court and the courts of
appeal to enter into cooperative agreements to develop a system that integrates all appellate
courts with a statewide LCRAA electronic filing platform.
Proposed law imposes an additional fee of $5 for documents recorded in accordance with
LCRAA. Requires LCRAA to remit the funds from the collected fee to the Court
Modernization and Technology Fund for the purpose of developing the statewide electronic
filing platform.
Proposed law requires LCRAA to provide a report to the legislature on the amount collected
from the fee and the progress of the integrated filing platform. Further requires submission
of the report no later than the start of R.S. 2028.
